text:
Thirty traits we have generally learned from the developments of the last 5 years
05 Nov 2019 by Asr Iran

The Middle East doesn't have much in common with us / There is a treasure trove called the human experience / There is no virtue higher than having "one personality".




Iran's Era - Dr. Mahmoud Jahr al-Qalam, a professor at Shahid Beheshti University, wrote in a note "Thirty features that we have generally learned from the developments of the last 7 years" and wrote:

1. Governance expertise is the most sophisticated expertise;
2. The most important form of governance is container knowledge and global dynamics;
3. Understanding this dish seems to have three prerequisites: extensive study of social, political, and economic texts, mastery of the English language, and a mathematical and genuine understanding of internal capacities;
4. Do not export too much oil and gas but use them for industrialization and production / export of goods;
5. Everyone should have only one job;
6. Politics is about thinking about the future: we just have to learn from the past;
7. The Middle East doesn't have much in common with us;
8. A developing country with a growth rate below 3% is deprived of reasonable living;
9. Get rich outside government circuits;
10. The most effective way to penetrate other countries is to enter their markets;
11. We are a highly pluralistic society, so that we can make room for one another;
12. Humiliating others is not free;
13. Reduce our strange need for "show off";
14. Putting yourself at the center of gravity is the result of not reading;
15. Consider the concept of "economic stability" and its requirements the center of governance;
16. Without the cooperation of citizens, no country will be built;
17. Expand our tolerance circuits so that millions do not migrate;
17. There is no virtue higher than having a "personality";
19. The Two Most Important Issues for Combating Individualism: Pride and Anger;
20. Let the media and reporters in a responsible way prevent the repetition of the mistakes of the performers;
21. If a manager stays in a project for more than eight years, it loses its effectiveness;
22. Conflict with great powers is very costly: 1, 2, 2, 2, 2 ... ؛
23. Life is not just about power but full of artistic beauty, nature and coexistence;
24. Nature severely punishes the liar;
25. The Most Reliable Way to Fight Corruption: Strengthen the Legislature;
26. Let's not change too much: morality means fulfilling the covenant;
27. Let us study self-study and struggle with pride and self-conceit;
28. Enjoy gardening as much as the Ministry;
29. Consider environmental protection a principle in life;
30. There is a treasure trove of human experience.
